<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/22098021-jill"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1484093051i/22098021._UX100_CR0,8,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/22098021-jill">Jill</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    I am so glad you asked this question because I was going to ask it! I think it pertains to Rachel. Rachel knew before anyone else and Rachel was the o<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    I am so glad you asked this question because I was going to ask it! I think it pertains to Rachel. Rachel knew before anyone else and Rachel was the one who took vigilante action leading to the arrest of Joanna. And I don't necessarily think this is relevant (but it could be) the book cover has the word "SHE" in the largest font as if to communicate that perhaps SHE is singular. <a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
